cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a scheme to improve energy efficiency in a wireless communication system (UMTS HSDPA). 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves estimating the energy efficiency under different modulation and coding schemes. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a power control scheme to optimize the energy efficiency of the system. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses improving user experience in HSDPA, which is related to multimedia applications. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve hardware implementation of the proposed scheme.
